145
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,215
No, I have not.

146
00:12:37,323 --> 00:12:41,020
Well, then I will present you with
a signed first edition when next we meet.

147
00:12:41,127 --> 00:12:45,029
It's my understanding you were educated
in Edinburgh, Scotland and Paris, France.

148
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:48,225
- That is correct.
- Good. The commodore likes an educated man.

149
00:12:48,334 --> 00:12:51,770
And there he is,
the most powerful man on earth.

150
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:54,066
<i>[Flies Buzzing]</i>

151
00:12:54,173 --> 00:12:57,836
<i>Don't be nervous, Colonel. </i>
<i>Just remember three things: </i>

152
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:02,209
Do not sit unless he invites you to,
always address him as "commodore"...

153
00:13:02,314 --> 00:13:05,750
and, under no circumstances,
ask for any personal favors.

154
00:13:05,851 --> 00:13:10,652
Commodore Cornelius Vanderbilt,
may I present Colonel William Walker?

155
00:13:10,756 --> 00:13:13,782
- Colonel of what?
- The American phalange in northern Mexico.

156
00:13:13,893 --> 00:13:15,861
