00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:13,006
<i>whom the popular press</i>
<i>saw fit to term "Walker's Immortals. "</i>

230
00:19:13,118 --> 00:19:16,087
<i>Walker, </i>
<i>I am Captain Siegfried Henningson... </i>

231
00:19:16,188 --> 00:19:19,089
late of the Corsican campaign
and the Balkan fiasco!

232
00:19:19,191 --> 00:19:21,591
I am well-schooled
in military matters, sir...

233
00:19:21,693 --> 00:19:24,161
<i>having studied with Josef Penn, </i>
<i>Lubitsch and von Koch.! </i>

234
00:19:24,263 --> 00:19:27,562
I would be honored, sir,
if you would accept my services.

235
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:31,932
I will, of course, provide for my own needs
and will require no financial assistance.

236
00:19:32,037 --> 00:19:33,766
What is your name again, sir?

237
00:19:33,872 --> 00:19:39,071
Lieutenant... Uh, Captain
Siegfried Henningson at your command, sir!

238
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:41,544
- You are now Major Henningson.
- <i>Sir.! </i>

239
00:19:41,647 --> 00:19:43,774
Cast off then!

240
00:19:43,882 --> 00:19:47,579
<i>[Walker Narrating] Never have I seen a collection</i>
<i>of such brave men assembled under one banner. </i>

241
00:19:48,754 --> 00:19:50,722
<i>God bless them all. </i>

242
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:13,807
<i>The American phalange landed</i>
<i>at Realejo, Nicaragua... </i>

243
00:20:13,912 --> 00:20:17,973
<i>where we were met by distinguished</i>
<i>representatives of the Nicaraguan Liberal Party. </i>

244
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:21,541
- My brother, William Walker.
- How do you do, sir?

245
00:20:21,653 --> 00:20:24,121
<i>[Walker Narrating]</i>
<i>These natives were to be our guides. </i>

246
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:27,850
- Aw, come on!
- Ow! My hair!

247
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:30,053
- Join the crowd.
- Jesus, stand up straight.

248
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:33,063
Start drumming, Mr. Turley.

249
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:37,295
* Oh, my darling Clementine *

250
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:41,771
- * You are lost and gone forever *
- [Women Laughing]

251
00:20:41,873 --> 00:20:46,003
* Dreadful sorry, Clementine **

252
00:20:46,111 --> 00:20:50,309
<i>[Walker Narrating] From the day the Americans</i>
<i>landed at Realejo dates a new era... </i>

253
00:20:50,415 --> 00:20:53,543
<i>not only for Nicaragua, </i>
<i>but for all Central America. </i>

254
00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:58,351
<i>* Oh, I went down South for to see my Sal</i>
<i>singing Polly wolly doodle all day *</i>

255
00:20:58,457 --> 00:21:01,392
- <i>*Because my Sal is a spunky gal *</i>
- <i>[Women Laughing]</i>

256
00:21:01,493 --> 00:21:03,393
<i>*Singing Polly wolly doodle all day *</i>

257
00:21:03,495 --> 00:21:06,430
- [Laughing Continues]
- <i>*Fare thee well, fare thee well *</i>

258
00:21:06,531 --> 00:21:09,557
<i>*Singing Polly wolly doodle all day *</i>

259
00:21:09,668 --> 00:21:12,398
<i>* Oh, I'm goin'to Louisiana</i>
<i>for to see my Susyanna *</i>

260
00:21:12,504 --> 00:21:15,439
- <i>*Singing Polly wolly doodle all day *</i>
- What are you doing?

261
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:17,633
- Move it!
- * Fare thee well, fare thee well **

262
00:21:17,743 --> 00:21:20,371
You're on my shit list, Washburn.

263
00:21:24,816 --> 00:21:26,716
Get up there.

264
00:21:35,694 --> 00:21:38,322
<i>[Man Shouting]</i>

265
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:41,126
Get over here, goddamn it!
<i>¡Vámonos.! </i>

266
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:44,794
<i>[Walker Narrating] We paused at the small, </i>
<i>unregenerated hamlet of Realejo... </i>

267
00:21:44,903 --> 00:21:47,303
<i>to await the arrival</i>
<i>of the leaders of the Liberal Party... </i>

268
00:21:47,406 --> 00:21:50,534
- Listen up here!
- <i>Generals Munoz and Castellon. </i>

269
00:21:52,377 --> 00:21:55,073
Proverbs, chapter 11, verse three.

270
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:57,876
"The integrity of the upright
shall guide them...

271
00:22:00,419 --> 00:22:02,819
"but the perverseness
of transgressors...

272
00:22:03,855 --> 00:22:05,755
shall destroy them."

273
00:22:05,857 --> 00:22:09,315
<i>Soldiers, we are now embarked</i>
<i>on a glorious destiny: </i>

274
00:22:11,096 --> 00:22:15,089
<i>nothing short of the entire</i>
<i>regeneration of this republic. </i>

275
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,532
<i>Ours is a sacred trust... </i>

276
00:22:17,636 --> 00:22:20,104
<i>and any man who betrays that trust... </i>

277
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:24,403
<i>by creating an act of transgression against</i>
<i>the hospitality of the Nicaraguan people... </i>

278
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:27,740
will be judged
and dealt with accordingly.

279
00:22:30,315 --> 00:22:32,749
There will be no excessive drinking...

280
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:35,786
<i>no seducing</i>
<i>and no swearing in public places. </i>

281
00:22:35,887 --> 00:22:37,912
What's that? That mean
we can swear in private?

282
00:22:38,023 --> 00:22:40,890
Quiet! The colonel's talking!

283
00:22:40,992 --> 00:22:42,892
Gentlemen...

284
00:22:44,062 --> 00:22:46,257
we are honored guests here...

285
00:22:47,799 --> 00:22:51,360
and we will act that way
according to the moral dictates of God...

286
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:54,030
science and hygiene.

287
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:56,767
- Hear. Hear.
- <i>That is all, Captain. </i>

288
00:22:56,875 --> 00:23:00,140
- Dismissed!
- [Cheering]

289
00:23:00,245 --> 00:23:02,213
What's the idea?

290
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:08,012
Hey, stop! Stop, stop.
Stop, stop!

291
00:23:27,305 --> 00:23:30,138
[Chickens Squawking]

292
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:45,221
Sanders, I know what you're thinking, but
believe me, even you can do better than that!

293
00:23:45,323 --> 00:23:49,555
Achilles, you just stay outta this!
The colonel says this is a democracy.

294
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:53,557
<i>[Bleating]</i>

295
00:23:53,665 --> 00:23:56,634
<i>[Walker Narrating] Walker realized</i>
<i>that he would need to keep a firm hand... </i>

296
00:23:56,735 --> 00:23:58,862
<i>on the moral conduct of the men. </i>

297
00:24:00,172 --> 00:24:02,663
Immortals!

298
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:07,178
<i>Aim.! </i>

299
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:13,850
Fire!

300
00:24:17,322 --> 00:24:19,222
Men...

301
00:24:19,324 --> 00:24:21,292
as of this moment...

302
00:24:22,327 --> 00:24:24,955
we do hereby, under God...

303
00:24:25,063 --> 00:24:27,122
become citizens of Nicaragua.

304
00:24:29,835 --> 00:24:32,861
<i>If there is any man who would say no</i>
<i>to this great privilege... </i>

305
00:24:32,971 --> 00:24:34,939
<i>let him step forward. </i>

306
00:24:41,379 --> 00:24:44,906
It is our mission to introduce into the family
of enlightened and civilized nations...

307
00:24:45,016 --> 00:24:47,211
a new sister.

308
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:50,254
To help us in our just cause...

309
00:24:50,355 --> 00:24:52,550
are two of Nicaragua's Liberal Party...

310
00:24:52,657 --> 00:24:54,784
and defenders of democracy...

311
00:24:56,261 --> 00:24:58,229
Generals...

312
00:24:59,598 --> 00:25:01,657
<i>Generals... </i>

313
00:25:01,766 --> 00:25:03,825
- [Whispers] Damn it.
- Castellon and Munoz.

314
00:25:03,935 --> 00:25:06,267
Castellon and Munoz.

315
00:25:06,371 --> 00:25:08,931
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Three cheers for the generals.! </i>

316
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,940
Three cheers for democracy!

317
00:25:11,042 --> 00:25:13,840
- Hip, hip!
- [Men Mumbling] Hooray.

318
00:25:13,945 --> 00:25:16,505
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray.

319
00:25:16,615 --> 00:25:19,516
- <i>Hip, hip.! </i>
- Hear! Hear!

320
00:25:19,618 --> 00:25:21,518
We march for Rivas.

321
00:25:21,620 --> 00:25:23,952
As God is on our side...

322
00:25:25,056 --> 00:25:27,024
victory will be ours.

323
00:25:27,125 --> 00:25:28,956
- Hurrah!
- <i>Rivas.! </i>

324
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:32,154
[Cheering, Whooping]

325
00:25:46,978 --> 00:25:48,946
[Shouts]

326
00:25:51,016 --> 00:25:52,711
Back!

327
00:26:00,992 --> 00:26:04,951
- [Squawking]
- [Screaming]

328
00:26:05,063 --> 00:26:07,190
It's a parrot, sir.

329
00:26:11,636 --> 00:26:14,400
<i>Watch your step.! Look out.! </i>

330
00:26:14,506 --> 00:26:16,701
Don't do that!

331
00:26:20,845 --> 00:26:23,006
Aw, shit!

332
00:26:33,525 --> 00:26:36,653
- [Man] What the hell?
- [British Accent] You chaps do crash about a bit.

333
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:39,389
- Lost your way, have you?
- We're marching to Rivas.

334
00:26:39,497 --> 00:26:41,829
Really? What on earth for?

335
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:44,561
We're liberatin' the country
for democracy.

336
00:26:44,669 --> 00:26:47,934
How very peculiar.
You must be American.

337
00:26:48,039 --> 00:26:51,440
Not no more.
We're Nicaraguans now.

338
00:26:51,543 --> 00:26:53,568
- You draw that?
- Yes.

339
00:26:53,678 --> 00:26:55,578
Why?

340
00:27:12,631 --> 00:27:14,758
- What do you think, Captain?
- I think we oughta...

341
00:27:14,866 --> 00:27:17,733
What do you think of these new guns?

342
00:27:17,836 --> 00:27:19,929
I like 'em.

343
00:27:20,038 --> 00:27:22,006
Six shots, and good-lookin' too.

344
00:27:22,107 --> 00:27:25,076
- I wish we had 'em for that firing squad.
- [Henningson] We wait until nightfall.

345
00:27:25,176 --> 00:27:28,168
Then we attack from the south
and from behind the church.

346
00:27:28,279 --> 00:27:31,112
- We will go straight in.
- That's right, Colonel. I'm with you all the way.

347
00:27:31,216 --> 00:27:34,982
Just jump right in and grab 'em by the throat.
Don't give 'em a chance to get set now.

348
00:27:35,086 --> 00:27:37,646
Excuse me, but haven't we just been assured
by Generals Castellon and Munoz...

349
00:27:37,756 --> 00:27:39,656
that we're to be met
with no resistance?

350
00:27:39,758 --> 00:27:42,226
Castellon is an indecisive old man.

351
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:44,693
Munoz is a conceited troublemaker.

352
00:27:44,796 --> 00:27:47,094
<i>William, forgive me, </i>
<i>but these men are our allies. </i>

353
00:27:47,198 --> 00:27:50,895
At any rate, we will go in hard
with our eyes open.

354
00:27:51,002 --> 00:27:53,300
First impression in a country
is very important.

355
00:27:53,405 --> 00:27:56,033
Forgive me, but this is idiotic.

356
00:27:56,141 --> 00:27:58,109
I prefer the last impression.

357
00:27:59,978 --> 00:28:01,946
First and last are often the same.

358
00:28:02,047 --> 00:28:04,481
<i>I didn't know</i>
<i>you were a pedant, Henningson. </i>

359
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:08,451
History never smiles on pedants.

360
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:10,453
Excuse me, gentlemen.

361
00:28:10,555 --> 00:28:13,023
Lieutenant, may I have
a word with you, please?

362
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:18,989
[Henningson Grunts] l, who have studied
military strategy with Lubitsch...

363
00:28:19,097 --> 00:28:22,362
Colonel, sir, could I have a word with you
one moment, uh, alone, sir?

364
00:28:22,467 --> 00:28:24,662
- Certainly.
- <i>[Man] Shut up, Henningson.! </i>

365
00:28:24,769 --> 00:28:27,237
- What seems to be the problem?
- Well, there's no problem, sir.

366
00:28:27,338 --> 00:28:30,466
I was just wonderin' though
perhaps maybe if, uh...

367
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:33,442
if I could be excused tomorrow
from being the drum major.

368
00:28:33,545 --> 00:28:36,673
It's just that every time I've seen
pictures of battlefield scenes...

369
00:28:36,781 --> 00:28:39,978
and, uh, I always see the drummer boy
lying dead next to his drum...

370
00:28:40,085 --> 00:28:43,054
and, uh, if it's all the same to you, sir...

371
00:28:43,154 --> 00:28:45,122
I'd like to trade my rifle in
for a drum.

372
00:28:45,223 --> 00:28:47,714
I mean, I'd like to trade
my drum in for a rifle.

373
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:52,991
As long as you are under my command,
no harm will come to you.

374
00:28:54,265 --> 00:28:56,165
Lieutenant.

375
00:28:57,902 --> 00:28:59,802
Straighten up.

376
00:29:05,744 --> 00:29:07,712
You wanted to see me, sir?

377
00:29:09,247 --> 00:29:12,876
Some men abandon all reason
before going into battle.

378
00:29:12,984 --> 00:29:15,316
They become so seized with fear that...

379
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:17,888
that often the battle is lost
before it's begun.

380
00:29:24,696 --> 00:29:27,164
I know this will not
happen with you, Timothy.

381
00:29:29,868 --> 00:29:31,995
Thank you for your confidence, sir.

382
00:29:34,539 --> 00:29:38,100
Sir, uh, I feel I have to tell you...

383
00:29:38,209 --> 00:29:41,667
The men are awfully confused about
just what exactly we're fightin' for here.

384
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:45,443
I mean... I mean, I know, and they know,
that the liberals are our friends...

385
00:29:45,550 --> 00:29:48,849
and the conservatives
are our enemies, but...

386
00:29:48,953 --> 00:29:52,286
well, to tell you the truth, sir,
I can't tell 'em apart.

387
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:54,358
They all seem the same to me.

388
00:29:54,459 --> 00:29:57,917
That is no concern of yours, Timothy,
nor of the men either.

389
00:30:00,064 --> 00:30:02,032
All you have to remember...

390
00:30:02,133 --> 00:30:04,761
is that our cause is a righteous one.

391
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:09,205
I know that, sir.

392
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:11,275
I hope you do, Timothy.

393
00:30:15,013 --> 00:30:16,981
I sincerely hope you do.

394
00:30:22,587 --> 00:30:24,214
Get some sleep.

395
00:30:26,057 --> 00:30:28,617
Yes, sir.

396
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:47,878
- <i>Come on.! </i>
- <i>[Walker] Turley, move 'em out.! </i>

397
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:45,802
- <i>[Shouts Echoing]</i>
- Above!

398
00:31:57,448 --> 00:32:00,008
<i>[Shouts, Gunshots Echoing]</i>

399
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:07,990
Come on!

400
00:32:10,528 --> 00:32:12,223
[Screaming]

401
00:32:13,598 --> 00:32:17,864
<i>Let's go, boys.! They won't know what to do</i>
<i>without us.! We need to split.! Let's go.! Move it.! </i>

402
00:32:17,969 --> 00:32:19,732
<i>Attack.! </i>

403
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:27,703
[Screaming]

404
00:32:56,007 --> 00:32:57,975
<i>[Gunfire Continues]</i>

405
00:32:58,076 --> 00:33:00,203
Colonel, what are you doing?

406
00:33:00,311 --> 00:33:02,609
I'm doing the only thing
I know how to do... advance!

407
00:33:02,714 --> 00:33:05,080
You dumb shit!

408
00:33:05,183 --> 00:33:09,051
There's no reason for you
to talk to me that way, Timothy.

409
00:33:09,153 --> 00:33:11,121
Sorry, sir.

410
00:33:14,592 --> 00:33:17,652
It's just you're gonna get yourself
and everyone else killed.

411
00:33:26,437 --> 00:33:28,405
Then we'll be together again,
won't we?

412
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:51,658
<i>[Man Shouting]</i>
<i>What the hell? Come on, go.! </i>

413
00:34:09,814 --> 00:34:12,146
We must get into a house, Colonel!

414
00:34:12,250 --> 00:34:14,218
- For God's sake, why?
- What?

415
00:34:14,318 --> 00:34:16,286
<i>For our own protection. </i>

416
00:34:18,122 --> 00:34:20,249
Yes. Yes.

417
00:34:21,359 --> 00:34:24,226
- Good idea, Major.
- Come, please! Come!

418
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:33,766
- [Walker] So, Dr. Jones, how is your day going?
- Just fine, William.

419
00:34:33,871 --> 00:34:36,305
We have 11 dead, several wounded.

420
00:34:36,407 --> 00:34:38,637
- How 'bout yourself?
- [Walker] Well, thank you.

421
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:41,735
Now that we have a plan, I feel sure
there will be a successful outcome.

422
00:34:41,846 --> 00:34:44,474
Splendid, William.

423
00:34:44,582 --> 00:34:46,550
- After you.
- No, no, no. I insist. After you.

424
00:34:46,651 --> 00:34:48,619
- No, please.
- Well, let's go in together.

425
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,619
Very well.

426
00:34:57,361 --> 00:34:59,761
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Colonel.! There's a room back here.! </i>

427
00:34:59,864 --> 00:35:02,492
- Is there a piano?
- <i>Yes, sir. </i>

428
00:35:03,701 --> 00:35:05,601
<i>[Gunfire Continues]</i>

429
00:35:05,703 --> 00:35:07,637
<i>Take care of the window.! </i>

430
00:35:07,738 --> 00:35:11,435
- Get your fat ass out of here!
- But I'm hungry!

431
00:35:11,542 --> 00:35:16,309
<i>[Man] Why don't you serve him</i>
<i>if you admire him? Follow him.! </i>

432
00:35:16,414 --> 00:35:18,314
God! I'm hungry!

433
00:35:19,617 --> 00:35:22,984
- You heathen!
- * Darling, I'm growing old *

434
00:35:23,087 --> 00:35:25,555
I'll shoot your eyes out!
[Laughing]

435
00:35:25,656 --> 00:35:27,851
- Goddamn music.
- * Silver threads **

436
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:30,484
[Screaming]

437
00:35:32,563 --> 00:35:35,464
<i>Get him out ofhere.! </i>

438
00:35:35,566 --> 00:35:38,501
Move it! Get him out!
Get him to a doctor!

439
00:35:38,603 --> 00:35:42,198
We need somebody to dig through
the walls. It's our only way!

440
00:35:42,306 --> 00:35:44,297
We don't have time.
We have to charge them bastards.

441
00:35:44,408 --> 00:35:46,467
- Rout 'em out like we did before.
- Dear God!

442
00:35:46,577 --> 00:35:48,477
- We have repeating rifles!
- [Henningson Shouting]

443
00:35:48,579 --> 00:35:51,548
- They have muskets!
- We shouldn't stand a chance!

444
00:35:51,649 --> 00:35:54,117
We're soldiers!
We kill people for a living!

445
00:35:54,218 --> 00:35:56,118
- Yes, sir!
- Shit!

446
00:35:57,755 --> 00:36:00,349
The colonel's leavin'!

447
00:36:00,458 --> 00:36:03,484
- Move out!
- <i>Come on.! </i>

448
00:36:03,594 --> 00:36:06,392
Men, we must leave immediately!

449
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:08,829
What about the wounded?

450
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:11,299
The wounded will have to
take their chances.

451
00:36:11,402 --> 00:36:14,394
- Go out the back when the charge goes off!
- You are not in command here!

452
00:36:14,505 --> 00:36:16,405
<i>You're right, Colonel.! </i>
<i>Forget about the wounded. Damn 'em.! </i>

453
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:19,101
We need another diversion. The men'll
charge through the hole after the blast.

454
00:36:19,210 --> 00:36:21,110
Nay, the powder
will be enough of a diversion!

455
00:36:21,212 --> 00:36:23,942
That is not my considered opinion, Major!

456
00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:26,243
- You men! You, you, you, you, you!
- <i>[Gunshot]</i>

457
00:36:26,350 --> 00:36:28,818
- After the blast, charge through the hole!
- I'll go when you go!

458
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:31,684
Everyone else, out the back!
We'll meet outside the town!

459
00:36:31,789 --> 00:36:35,156
Damn it! Fuck you, Colonel!
Benito's not goin' through no goddamn wall!

460
00:36:53,611 --> 00:36:55,374
Huh?

461
00:36:55,479 --> 00:36:57,310
- Major?
- <i>[Man] What? </i>

462
00:36:57,415 --> 00:37:00,543
<i>No way. Oh, wait, wait, wait.! Wait.! </i>

463
00:37:00,651 --> 00:37:03,017
- Open the door!
- The fuse is burning!

464
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:06,647
<i>[Screaming]</i>
<i>Oh, shit.! </i>

465
00:37:22,940 --> 00:37:25,306
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

466
00:37:37,154 --> 00:37:40,317
[Shouting In Spanish]

467
00:37:40,424 --> 00:37:42,517
[Child Shouts, Crying]

468
00:37:46,764 --> 00:37:48,425
[Spanish]

469
00:38:04,749 --> 00:38:07,081
[Crying]

470
00:38:26,771 --> 00:38:28,739
<i>[Crying Continues]</i>

471
00:38:39,917 --> 00:38:44,286
<i>[Walker Narrating] Suffering a temporary setback</i>
<i>and wishing to protect his men at all costs... </i>

472
00:38:44,388 --> 00:38:46,822
<i>Walker decided</i>
<i>to make a strategic withdrawal... </i>

473
00:38:46,924 --> 00:38:49,552
<i>to the seaport of San Juan del Sur. </i>

474
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:53,221
<i>As always, </i>
<i>his men's spirits remained high. </i>

475
00:38:54,832 --> 00:38:56,732
Dr. Jones.

476
00:38:57,902 --> 00:39:00,166
When you were a little boy...

477
00:39:01,539 --> 00:39:06,135
did you ever have a moment
when you were sitting outside on the lawn...

478
00:39:06,243 --> 00:39:09,303
and you picked up a blade of grass
or a beetle...

479
00:39:09,413 --> 00:39:11,381
and you just looked at it?

480
00:39:14,785 --> 00:39:18,812
And it was whole and perfect
and totally outside of time.

481
00:39:23,694 --> 00:39:27,653
<i>**[People Singing In Spanish]</i>

482
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:38,040
William!

483
00:39:40,644 --> 00:39:42,441
<i>Uh, Colonel, sir. </i>

484
00:39:42,546 --> 00:39:45,913
You're late, Cole!
You were supposed to come by sea.

485
00:39:46,016 --> 00:39:48,314
<i>But, Colonel, I brought new recruits. </i>

486
00:39:48,419 --> 00:39:51,547
<i>Prussian troops from Ecuador. </i>

487
00:39:51,655 --> 00:39:55,216
** [Singing, Indistinct]

488
00:39:55,326 --> 00:39:57,226
[Lowing]

489
00:39:58,429 --> 00:40:01,296
Magnificent tactics.

490
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:03,867
I commend you, General.

491
00:40:03,968 --> 00:40:06,903
What do you mean, "tactics"?
Who is this man?

492
00:40:07,004 --> 00:40:08,938
<i>Victoire, mon général. </i>

493
00:40:09,039 --> 00:40:11,633
I'm Bruno von Namzer.
<i>À votre service. </i>

494
00:40:11,742 --> 00:40:13,642
<i>Je vous salue. </i>

495
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:16,975
<i>Now, I take it, </i>
<i>you will invade Granada. </i>

496
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:20,812
- <i>You mean you don't know? </i>
- Know what?

497
00:40:20,918 --> 00:40:24,945
You have inflicted such heavy casualties
on the enemy that he has abandoned Rivas.

498
00:40:25,055 --> 00:40:28,252
His troops are racked
with dysentery and cholera.

499
00:40:28,359 --> 00:40:30,554
You broke their spirit, William.

500
00:40:30,661 --> 00:40:33,824
You are victorious.
You have won.

501
00:40:33,931 --> 00:40:35,831
We won!

502
00:40:35,933 --> 00:40:38,333
- [Cheering]
- [Horse Whinnying]

503
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:40,404
We have won!

504
00:40:42,373 --> 00:40:46,002
- We racked them with cholera and dysentery!
- Now is the hour of my destiny arrived.

505
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:48,977
- [Man Laughing] We've won!
- I cannot lose.

506
00:40:50,614 --> 00:40:54,448
<i>[Walker Narrating] Determined to end</i>
<i>the civil war and reconcile the divided nation... </i>

507
00:40:54,552 --> 00:40:58,352
<i>we marched upon Granada, </i>
<i>a bastion of conservative power. </i>

508
00:40:58,456 --> 00:41:01,186
<i>**[Drum, Tin Whistle]</i>

509
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:03,988
<i>The American phalange</i>
<i>entered the capital at dawn... </i>

510
00:41:04,094 --> 00:41:06,062
<i>where we were welcomed</i>
<i>as liberators. </i>

511
00:41:12,169 --> 00:41:14,069
Captain Hornsby?

512
00:41:14,171 --> 00:41:17,766
<i>[Hornsby]</i>
<i>Immortals, charge.! Charge.! </i>

513
00:41:17,875 --> 00:41:20,343
[Men Shouting, Whooping]

514
00:41:26,050 --> 00:41:28,075
Watch it! Come on, Hornsby.

515
00:41:28,185 --> 00:41:30,983
Here... You must...
Goddamn it! My arm!

516
00:41:31,088 --> 00:41:33,215
<i>Captain Hornsby. </i>

517
00:41:33,324 --> 00:41:35,224
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Get out of the house.! </i>

518
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:39,057
- Captain Hornsby, I must object...
- <i>[Man] Take 'em, boys.! Tag 'em and bag 'em.! </i>

519
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:41,791
<i>[Bells Chiming]</i>

520
00:41:41,899 --> 00:41:45,596
- <i>[Woman Screaming]</i>
- <i>[Gunfire]</i>

521
00:41:45,703 --> 00:41:48,399
Quiet, you ammo firers!

522
00:41:48,506 --> 00:41:51,498
Listen up!
Colonel's about to speak!

523
00:41:51,609 --> 00:41:54,169
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Dismount the prisoners.! </i>

524
00:41:54,278 --> 00:41:56,246
Citizens of Nicaragua!

525
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:58,713
Today the city of Granada...

526
00:41:58,816 --> 00:42:00,977
and the entire country of Nicaragua
have been liberated.

527
00:42:01,085 --> 00:42:02,677
<i>[Few Men]</i>
<i>Hooray.! </i>

528
00:42:02,786 --> 00:42:07,018
It is our sacred duty to join together
and unify this great nation.

529
00:42:07,124 --> 00:42:11,288
<i>Today, however, </i>
<i>is a day of celebration. </i>

530
00:42:11,395 --> 00:42:13,124
- Tomorrow we must...
- <i>[Gunshot]</i>

531
00:42:13,230 --> 00:42:15,460
- Colonel!
- [Shouts In French]

532
00:42:15,566 --> 00:42:17,193
Fire!

533
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:20,498
<i>[Bruno]</i>
<i>Shoot the prisoners.! Kill them.! Kill them.! </i>

534
00:42:29,914 --> 00:42:31,814
<i>[Body Thuds]</i>

535
00:42:34,084 --> 00:42:35,984
<i>[Crowd Gasping]</i>

536
00:42:41,058 --> 00:42:44,152
It is not my time to die!

537
00:42:44,261 --> 00:42:47,230
[Together]
It is not his time to die!

538
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:54,762
The assassin's bullet
has struck correspondence...

539
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:58,069
from that great Nicaraguan patriot
General Castellon!

540
00:43:00,344 --> 00:43:03,074
It is he who has saved my life...

541
00:43:04,148 --> 00:43:08,642
as it is I who shall save
the life of this country!

542
00:43:08,752 --> 00:43:11,653
- <i>[Men Cheering]</i>
- [Speaking Spanish]

543
00:43:16,660 --> 00:43:18,093
<i>[Men]</i>
<i>Walker.! Walker.! Walker.! </i>

544
00:43:22,232 --> 00:43:24,700
<i>Walker.! Walker.! Walker.! Walker.! </i>

545
00:43:24,802 --> 00:43:28,704
- [Spanish]
- <i>We want Walker.! We want Walker.! </i>

546
00:43:28,806 --> 00:43:31,366
<i>We want Walker.! Walker.! Walker.! </i>

547
00:43:31,609 --> 00:43:34,669
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Colonel Walker, we are here to thank you... </i>

548
00:43:34,778 --> 00:43:37,076
from the deepest of our hearts...

549
00:43:37,181 --> 00:43:40,548
- <i>[Man Coughing]</i>
- [Woman Speaking Spanish]

550
00:43:42,086 --> 00:43:44,680
for the ending of our civil war...

551
00:43:44,788 --> 00:43:46,813
[Spanish Continues]

552
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:51,257
and bringing us the precious gift...

553
00:43:51,362 --> 00:43:53,296
<i>of freedom. </i>

554
00:43:53,397 --> 00:43:55,024
- Hear. Hear.
- Hear. Hear.

555
00:43:55,132 --> 00:43:56,599
- Hear. Hear.
- Hear. Hear.

556
00:43:56,700 --> 00:43:58,930
What are we doing here?

557
00:43:59,036 --> 00:44:01,334
[Spanish]

558
00:44:04,742 --> 00:44:07,210
What are your intentions...

559
00:44:07,311 --> 00:44:11,145
toward the office of the presidency?

560
00:44:11,248 --> 00:44:14,115
Turn it down
and offer it to Corral.

561
00:44:14,218 --> 00:44:16,516
You'll own him,
and everyone will be happy.

562
00:44:16,620 --> 00:44:19,589
Tell 'em you'll take
commander in chief of the armed forces.

563
00:44:26,263 --> 00:44:28,788
I am deeply grateful
for the extraordinary privilege...

564
00:44:28,899 --> 00:44:31,663
of being offered
such an exalted position.

565
00:44:33,270 --> 00:44:35,738
However, I must regretfully decline.

566
00:44:38,942 --> 00:44:41,069
It would be more beneficial
to the country...

567
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:44,113
if Walker were to protect
the democratic process...

568
00:44:44,214 --> 00:44:47,115
as commander in chief
of the armed forces.

569
00:44:47,217 --> 00:44:49,412
<i>[Chattering, Laughing]</i>

570
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:52,853
- Yeah!
- The army. Now we're talkin'.

571
00:44:52,956 --> 00:44:56,084
I would therefore
like to nominate as president...

572
00:44:56,193 --> 00:44:58,627
a great hero and patriot.

573
00:45:06,370 --> 00:45:08,338
General Ponciano Corral.

574
00:45:08,439 --> 00:45:10,737
[Shouts In Spanish]

575
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:25,620
- Walker! Walker!
- <i>[Gunshot]</i>

576
00:45:25,723 --> 00:45:27,623
<i>[Cheering Continues]</i>

577
00:45:28,726 --> 00:45:31,251
- <i>[Gunshot]</i>
- <i>[Applause]</i>

578
00:45:40,337 --> 00:45:42,464
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Colonel Walker.! </i>

579
00:45:43,607 --> 00:45:45,507
<i>[Popping Sound]</i>

580
00:45:48,746 --> 00:45:52,079
<i>Your country is primitive, </i>
<i>but it's full of possibilities... </i>

581
00:45:52,182 --> 00:45:54,150
for democratic advancement.

582
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:56,151
<i>[Fireworks Popping]</i>

583
00:45:57,621 --> 00:46:01,387
[Spanish]

584
00:46:05,696 --> 00:46:08,927
We must first establish agrarian reforms
before we proceed...

585
00:46:09,032 --> 00:46:12,524
<i>to equalize the social classes, </i>
<i>and above all... </i>

586
00:46:13,837 --> 00:46:17,432
<i>We must separate church and state. </i>
<i>Don't you think? </i>

587
00:46:17,541 --> 00:46:19,441
[Chuckles]

588
00:46:30,921 --> 00:46:34,118
<i>Yes. We must make English</i>
<i>the official language... </i>

589
00:46:34,224 --> 00:46:38,024
<i>so as to end discrimination</i>
<i>against Americans. </i>

590
00:46:38,128 --> 00:46:40,096
<i>We will end conscription. </i>

591
00:46:41,131 --> 00:46:45,158
Release the natives from the army
so that they may resupply the labor force.

592
00:46:45,269 --> 00:46:47,169
The Amer...

593
00:46:48,505 --> 00:46:50,439
The American phalange will...

594
00:46:51,742 --> 00:46:54,939
<i>be responsible for national security. </i>

595
00:46:55,045 --> 00:46:59,948
<i>And I do think we should provide</i>
<i>for free elections within the next six months. </i>

596
00:47:00,984 --> 00:47:02,952
<i>If you think that's possible. </i>

597
00:47:19,570 --> 00:47:22,004
You must be patient with me,
Doña Yrena.

598
00:47:24,675 --> 00:47:26,973
I'm a shy man in these matters.

599
00:47:58,542 --> 00:48:00,510
[Speaking Spanish]

600
00:48:25,969 --> 00:48:28,938
[Moans]

601
00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:37,341
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>What are you guys doing? </i>

602
00:48:37,447 --> 00:48:39,415
[Shouting In Spanish]

603
00:48:39,516 --> 00:48:41,643
- <i>[Man Shouts In Spanish]</i>
- Look at that!

604
00:48:41,752 --> 00:48:46,155
<i>[Walker Narrating] Walker's Immortals</i>
<i>initiated various cultural and civic reforms... </i>

605
00:48:46,256 --> 00:48:50,056
<i>including the construction of a theater</i>
<i>in the traditional European style. </i>

606
00:48:50,160 --> 00:48:52,788
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>I went to that shanty you callin'a house. </i>

607
00:48:52,896 --> 00:48:55,888
<i>I went to give the girls a bath. </i>
<i>There was no water. </i>

608
00:48:55,999 --> 00:48:58,467
No water on Tuesday?

609
00:48:58,568 --> 00:49:02,197
There was also no toilet paper,
no beer.

610
00:49:02,306 --> 00:49:06,868
- This is Managua?
- No, this is Granada.

611
00:49:06,977 --> 00:49:09,502
- Look at 'em floggin' those kids!
- Come on!

612
00:49:09,613 --> 00:49:13,879
<i>[Walker Narrating] Walker, seeking literacy</i>
<i>above all other gods save hygiene... </i>

613
00:49:13,984 --> 00:49:16,953
<i>started a newspaper, </i>
El Nicaraguense.

614
00:49:17,054 --> 00:49:20,023
I know that guy.
He owes me seven bucks.

615
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:23,320
Next thing you know,
they'll be institutin' slavery.

616
00:49:23,427 --> 00:49:27,158
It's the same racist, macho, sexist shit
we turned our backs on.

617
00:49:28,198 --> 00:49:30,826
It doesn't have
the feel of victory in it.

618
00:49:32,135 --> 00:49:35,002
It should be glorious and proud,
like the French revolution.

619
00:49:35,105 --> 00:49:37,903
- Yeah, I think so too.
- But that's the way it was.

620
00:49:38,008 --> 00:49:40,476
- <i>That's beside the point, Mr. Doubleday. </i>
- Well, what do you think?

621
00:49:40,577 --> 00:49:43,603
- Shall I send a copy to the commodore?
- <i>[Walker] Yes, absolutely, Byron. </i>

622
00:49:43,714 --> 00:49:47,741
- And ask him for more money, if you would.
- <i>[Man]James, come on. </i>

623
00:49:47,851 --> 00:49:51,480
<i>Come on, come on. </i>
<i>Hey, Billy, my man.! </i>

624
00:49:51,588 --> 00:49:54,182
Top gringo
and heavyweight generalissimo!

625
00:49:54,291 --> 00:49:56,623
[Laughing]
We're his brothers.

626
00:49:56,727 --> 00:50:00,527
- Really? I didn't know he had any brothers.
- Well, he does, okay?

627
00:50:00,630 --> 00:50:02,860
William, we came down
as soon as we heard.

628
00:50:02,966 --> 00:50:06,299
Everybody's talking about you in the States.
You're famous, man!

629
00:50:06,403 --> 00:50:09,839
Yes, James.
Well, that's all relative, of course.

630
00:50:11,875 --> 00:50:13,843
If you'll excuse me,
I have work to do.

631
00:50:13,944 --> 00:50:16,412
Well, wait just a minute.

632
00:50:16,513 --> 00:50:20,244
You know, we've been on the road for months
here comin' down here to help you out.

633
00:50:20,350 --> 00:50:21,817
Yeah!

634
00:50:21,918 --> 00:50:24,284
<i>And all you can say</i>
<i>is you have a lot of work to do? </i>

635
00:50:24,388 --> 00:50:26,356
Yes. That's all I can say.

636
00:50:29,526 --> 00:50:31,517
If you will excuse me.

637
00:50:31,628 --> 00:50:33,653
Come on, come on, come on.

638
00:50:33,764 --> 00:50:36,232
Maybe when you get some time, huh?

639
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:40,837
It's good to see you, James.

640
00:50:42,139 --> 00:50:44,039
You too.

641
00:50:48,612 --> 00:50:51,843
<i>[Moaning]</i>

642
00:50:51,948 --> 00:50:53,848
- <i>[Whip Cracking]</i>
- <i>[Man Screaming]</i>

643
00:50:53,950 --> 00:50:57,249
- [Moaning Continues]
- <i>[Bell Tolling]</i>

644
00:51:00,657 --> 00:51:02,557
Ellen.

645
00:51:04,895 --> 00:51:07,022
Oh, Ellie.

646
00:51:07,130 --> 00:51:09,394
Oh, Ellie.

647
00:51:09,499 --> 00:51:11,467
- [Spanish]
- Oh, Ellie.

648
00:51:14,838 --> 00:51:16,738
[Moaning Continues]

649
00:51:28,151 --> 00:51:30,051
Willians.

650
00:51:30,153 --> 00:51:32,348
<i>[Gunfire]</i>

651
00:51:32,456 --> 00:51:35,789
<i>[Man Shouting In Spanish]</i>

652
00:51:35,892 --> 00:51:38,656
- <i>[Bell Tolling]</i>
- <i>[Shouting Continues]</i>

653
00:51:40,097 --> 00:51:42,565
- <i>[Whip Cracking]</i>
- <i>[Man Screaming]</i>

654
00:51:44,301 --> 00:51:47,099
- [Tolling Continues]
- <i>[Whip Cracking Continues]</i>

655
00:51:47,204 --> 00:51:49,672
<i>[Screaming Continues]</i>

656
00:51:51,241 --> 00:51:54,142
[Weeping, Screaming]

657
00:51:57,280 --> 00:51:59,475
One must act with severity...

658
00:51:59,583 --> 00:52:02,211
or perish.

659
00:52:02,319 --> 00:52:05,618
What are you... Hey!
Put that... Put that down!

660
00:52:05,722 --> 00:52:08,088
What are you, some kind of hick?

661
00:52:08,191 --> 00:52:10,887
And don't give me that look!

662
00:52:10,994 --> 00:52:13,554
<i>I bring you down here</i>
<i>to the Paris, France of Central America... </i>

663
00:52:13,663 --> 00:52:17,861
and you're behaving like you're still
in some hamlet in the woods some...

664
00:52:17,968 --> 00:52:20,266
[Man Chattering]

665
00:52:20,370 --> 00:52:23,828
[Man] There's power for you, huh?
Man doesn't even recognize his own brother.

666
00:52:23,940 --> 00:52:25,965
[Laughing]

667
00:52:26,076 --> 00:52:28,271
[Walker]
What about Honduras and Costa Rica, Byron?

668
00:52:28,378 --> 00:52:30,505
- Hey.
- <i>Don't you think they need democracy too? </i>

669
00:52:30,614 --> 00:52:32,639
- Hey.
- <i>[Cole] Try to pay attention</i>
<i>to the matter at hand. </i>

670
00:52:32,749 --> 00:52:35,650
- Hey! Hey, hey, hey!
- Vanderbilt's plans are with Nicaragua...

671
00:52:35,752 --> 00:52:37,720
Who the hell
do you think you are, Willie?

672
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:39,789
I'm your goddamn brother!

673
00:52:39,890 --> 00:52:42,950
You throw me a bone, for Christ's sake!

674
00:52:43,059 --> 00:52:46,460
Don't you ever talk to me that way
in public again.

675
00:52:46,563 --> 00:52:48,656
You are welcome here
only if you contribute.

676
00:52:48,765 --> 00:52:51,563
I have many brothers here,
and they're all equal in my eyes...

677
00:52:51,668 --> 00:52:55,627
Don't give me that bullshit!
I don't believe in equality and neither do you!

678
00:52:55,739 --> 00:52:58,173
You make me an officer
and give me some money...

679
00:52:58,275 --> 00:53:02,006
or, by God, I'll stink up the place.

680
00:53:03,713 --> 00:53:06,443
- [Kisses]
- Yeah! Yeah.

681
00:53:06,550 --> 00:53:09,610
You and James will be lieutenants.
Nothing more until you earn it.

682
00:53:11,388 --> 00:53:13,288
[Whispers In Spanish]

683
00:53:13,390 --> 00:53:17,349
<i>What about the money, Willie? </i>
<i>Put me in charge of the treasury.! </i>

684
00:53:18,562 --> 00:53:20,894
[Walker]
Get out of my way!

685
00:53:22,532 --> 00:53:25,797
Boys, he made me a general.
You're a corporal.

686
00:53:28,138 --> 00:53:32,507
<i>[Walker Narrating] Walker realized that</i>
<i>he could no longer trust his former allies. </i>

687
00:53:32,609 --> 00:53:37,205
<i>In particular, he determined to keep</i>
<i>a sharp watch on so</i>-<i>called President Corral. </i>

688
00:53:37,314 --> 00:53:39,214
[Snarls]

689
00:53:43,520 --> 00:53:45,613
<i>[Man Speaking Spanish]</i>

690
00:53:45,889 --> 00:53:48,858
<i>[Man #2 Speaking Spanish]</i>

691
00:53:49,526 --> 00:53:51,585
[Spanish]

692
00:54:20,991 --> 00:54:23,050
I have an interesting letter here, sir.

693
00:54:30,100 --> 00:54:32,000
"Lost is Nicaragua.

694
00:54:32,102 --> 00:54:35,469
"Lost Honduras,
Salvador and Guatemala too...

695
00:54:36,573 --> 00:54:39,838
unless we all unite
against the gringo."

696
00:54:48,118 --> 00:54:50,586
I want you to arrest Corral.

697
00:54:50,687 --> 00:54:53,019
<i>[Hornsby]</i>
<i>Of course, sir. </i>

698
00:54:54,524 --> 00:54:56,583
Assure him he will
receive a fair trial.

699
00:54:56,693 --> 00:54:58,854
<i>Don't worry, Colonel. </i>
<i>We'll take care ofhim. </i>

700
00:55:03,266 --> 00:55:06,292
William, want me to join 'em?

701
00:55:08,071 --> 00:55:10,198
You'd better hurry, James.

702
00:55:21,584 --> 00:55:24,485
[Spanish]

703
00:55:24,587 --> 00:55:29,047
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Execution souvenirs, medallions. </i>

704
00:55:29,159 --> 00:55:32,754
<i>[Walker Narrating] Corral was found guilty</i>
<i>of treason and sentenced to die. </i>

705
00:55:32,862 --> 00:55:35,831
<i>The entire country</i>
<i>rejoiced at this news. </i>

706
00:55:35,932 --> 00:55:39,698
<i>There was no doubt in anybody's mind</i>
<i>thatjustice had been served. </i>

707
00:55:43,673 --> 00:55:46,039
William.

708
00:55:46,142 --> 00:55:48,576
[Spanish]

709
00:55:48,678 --> 00:55:50,578
<i>[Munoz]</i>
Yrena, por favor.

710
00:55:53,550 --> 00:55:57,384
General Walker, Corral is
like a father to his people.

711
00:55:57,487 --> 00:56:00,923
Then he is a tyrannical father
who would betray his children.

712
00:56:01,024 --> 00:56:04,050
<i>He was calling on foreign troops</i>
<i>to start an insurrection. </i>

713
00:56:04,160 --> 00:56:07,857
Treason must be punished.
I have no choice.

714
00:56:07,964 --> 00:56:10,489
[Spanish]

715
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:13,398
[Spanish]

716
00:56:16,873 --> 00:56:20,468
[Shouting In Spanish]

717
00:56:22,846 --> 00:56:28,079
Doña Yrena says that it's...
it's a terrible mistake to kill Corral.

718
00:56:28,184 --> 00:56:33,247
A mistake, General.
In this case, I entirely agree with her.

719
00:56:33,356 --> 00:56:35,517
Morally, as well as politically.

720
00:56:35,625 --> 00:56:39,152
You will lose everything
you have gained... up to now.

721
00:56:39,262 --> 00:56:41,389
She said something else.

722
00:56:41,498 --> 00:56:45,025
She called me a name.
What did she call me?

723
00:56:45,135 --> 00:56:48,298
She called you a dog's asshole.

724
00:56:50,974 --> 00:56:53,204
You know they are right, William.

725
00:56:53,309 --> 00:56:56,437
If you persist in this,
everyone will hate you.

726
00:56:56,546 --> 00:56:58,480
I cannot help that.

727
00:56:58,581 --> 00:57:01,982
Sometimes a leader must listen
to a higher law.

728
00:57:03,119 --> 00:57:06,179
What you say may be true, but it
is not, in the final view, important.

729
00:57:06,289 --> 00:57:08,883
- Listen to reason.
- I ask you never to speak of this matter again!

730
00:57:08,992 --> 00:57:11,483
- If you want my opinion...
- <i>[Cole And Bruno] Enough.! </i>

731
00:57:15,398 --> 00:57:18,925
General Corral shall not be
executed today at noon.

732
00:57:19,035 --> 00:57:21,469
[Speaking Spanish]

733
00:57:24,073 --> 00:57:27,099
He shall be executed
this afternoon at 2:00.

734
00:57:27,210 --> 00:57:30,338
<i>[Translator Speaking Spanish]</i>

735
00:57:33,116 --> 00:57:35,016
<i>Muy bien. </i>

736
00:57:35,118 --> 00:57:37,018
<i>Gracias. </i>

737
00:58:09,752 --> 00:58:12,516
- [Sobbing]
- [Men Shouting In Spanish]

738
00:58:14,657 --> 00:58:16,625
[Spanish]

739
00:58:16,726 --> 00:58:19,786
[Shouting]

740
00:58:19,896 --> 00:58:21,989
[Spanish]

741
00:58:25,301 --> 00:58:27,929
<i>[Man Shouting Orders]</i>

742
00:58:32,375 --> 00:58:34,343
[Shouting Orders]

743
00:58:36,179 --> 00:58:38,079
Fire!

744
00:58:48,091 --> 00:58:50,423
<i>[Man Speaking Spanish]</i>

745
00:58:51,661 --> 00:58:53,629
<i>[Woman Wailing]</i>

746
00:59:09,612 --> 00:59:13,844
- <i>[Hornsby] That son of a bitch has taken off. </i>
- <i>[Henningson] Probably Costa Rica. </i>

747
00:59:13,950 --> 00:59:17,579
- <i>[Cole] We need to find him and bring him back. </i>
- A few rides after his funeral...

748
00:59:17,687 --> 00:59:20,212
<i>[Hornsby] Do you know what it's like</i>
<i>out there in that damn country? </i>

749
00:59:20,323 --> 00:59:22,416
<i>[Cole]</i>
<i>I may not, but I know what it's like here... </i>

750
00:59:22,525 --> 00:59:24,425
and I know we're in trouble
without a president.

751
00:59:24,527 --> 00:59:28,930
- Gentlemen, if you want my view...
- I don't, actually. And neither does anyone else.

752
00:59:29,032 --> 00:59:32,331
No need to get a wild hair
up your ass, Mr. Cole.

753
00:59:32,435 --> 00:59:35,199
I was only making a suggestion.

754
00:59:36,306 --> 00:59:38,934
Gentlemen, gentlemen.

755
00:59:42,412 --> 00:59:45,347
Perhaps the time has come
for an election.

756
00:59:45,448 --> 00:59:48,349
<i>There has already been an election. </i>

757
00:59:51,387 --> 00:59:53,287
I won.

758
01:00:06,035 --> 01:00:09,698
<i>Gentlemen, the morning paper. </i>

759
01:00:09,806 --> 01:00:12,468
- <i>[Walker] Thank you, Mr. Rudler. </i>
- Yes, sir.

760
01:00:12,575 --> 01:00:15,874
- <i>[Man Speaking German]</i>
- <i>[Man #2] Congratulations, Mr. President. </i>

761
01:00:15,979 --> 01:00:18,777
<i>[Walker]</i>
<i>James. </i>

762
01:00:18,881 --> 01:00:22,373
[Henningson]
What has this man done to my newspaper?

763
01:00:22,485 --> 01:00:24,510
[Rudler Laughing]

764
01:00:30,226 --> 01:00:32,194
<i>[Birds Chirping]</i>

765
01:01:05,294 --> 01:01:07,956
<i>**[Car Radio: Up</i>-<i>tempo Latin]</i>

766
01:01:08,064 --> 01:01:11,966
- <i>**[Man Singing, Indistinct]</i>
- <i>[Crowd Chattering]</i>

767
01:01:12,068 --> 01:01:13,797
[Shouting, Chattering]

768
01:01:13,903 --> 01:01:15,871
<i>**[Continues]</i>

769
01:01:20,977 --> 01:01:24,037
You're quite a hero
back in the United States, General.

770
01:01:25,148 --> 01:01:27,343
Do you have any plans to go back?

771
01:01:27,450 --> 01:01:31,477
Nicaragua is my country. As long as
I am needed here, I will never leave.

772
01:01:31,587 --> 01:01:33,885
Your country is in a state of chaos.

773
01:01:33,990 --> 01:01:36,550
Guerrilla wars are taking place.

774
01:01:36,659 --> 01:01:40,652
And yet, you refuse
to engage the enemy. Why?

775
01:01:40,763 --> 01:01:43,698
A protracted war against
scattered guerrilla groups...

776
01:01:43,800 --> 01:01:47,395
would not only be disheartening
and dissatisfying...

777
01:01:47,503 --> 01:01:50,404
but it would be too exhausting
for our American troops.

778
01:01:50,506 --> 01:01:52,440
Have you anything to say
to the American people?

779
01:01:52,542 --> 01:01:54,442
I certainly do.

780
01:01:54,544 --> 01:01:58,071
Climb on board one of Commodore Vanderbilt's
steamships and come on down and see us.

781
01:01:58,181 --> 01:02:02,618
<i>[Man] The truth is, President Walker, that</i>
<i>Cornelius Vanderbilt is taking advantage of you. </i>

782
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:04,710
His transit company,
which guarantees overland passage...

783
01:02:04,821 --> 01:02:06,846
from the Atlantic to the Pacific...

784
01:02:06,956 --> 01:02:09,117
is not paying you what they should.

785
01:02:09,225 --> 01:02:13,525
He is, to put it bluntly,
exploiting you and the entire country.

786
01:02:13,629 --> 01:02:15,529
Shame, shame.

787
01:02:17,433 --> 01:02:19,594
Why are you telling me this?

788
01:02:19,702 --> 01:02:23,900
Simply put, we propose to start a new company
and make you an even better offer.

789
01:02:24,006 --> 01:02:27,339
But to do this, you must
revoke Vanderbilt's license...

790
01:02:27,443 --> 01:02:31,402
and grant our company one instead...
on most favorable terms, of course.

791
01:02:31,514 --> 01:02:35,348
You're telling me that Vanderbilt has
not been paying me what he owes me?

792
01:02:35,451 --> 01:02:37,919
<i>There's no question about that. </i>

793
01:02:38,020 --> 01:02:40,386
- That is inexcusable.
- <i>[Cole] No doubt. </i>

794
01:02:40,490 --> 01:02:44,085
<i>But we mustn't forget that</i>
<i>without Cornelius Vanderbilt... </i>

795
01:02:44,193 --> 01:02:46,093
we wouldn't be here today.

796
01:02:46,195 --> 01:02:49,995
That's true. Whatever good fortune
we have, we owe it to him.

797
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:53,694
Not only that, but he would be
a terrible man to cross.

798
01:03:02,712 --> 01:03:06,045
I hardly think, gentlemen...

799
01:03:08,518 --> 01:03:10,418
that Commodore Vanderbilt...

800
01:03:11,454 --> 01:03:14,753
is responsible for my great...
our great victories in the field.

801
01:03:15,792 --> 01:03:19,922
May I have a word with you, please,
William? I mean, Mr. President.

802
01:03:20,029 --> 01:03:22,691
Certainly, Byron. Anything
you wish to say, you may say here.

803
01:03:22,799 --> 01:03:27,361
Walker does not resort
to whispers and subterfuge.

804
01:03:29,705 --> 01:03:33,072
Our great victories
notwithstanding, William...

805
01:03:33,176 --> 01:03:35,940
we are utterly dependent
upon Cornelius Vanderbilt.

806
01:03:36,045 --> 01:03:38,138
His ships are our lifeline
to the United States.

807
01:03:38,247 --> 01:03:41,876
They provide us with money,
munitions, medicine and men.

808
01:03:41,984 --> 01:03:44,612
We cannot risk
incurring his displeasure.

809
01:03:47,089 --> 01:03:50,388
Traitor! Traitor! Traitor!

810
01:04:03,439 --> 01:04:05,498
Gentlemen...

811
01:04:05,608 --> 01:04:08,133
it was granted to me
in our recent constitution...

812
01:04:08,244 --> 01:04:11,475
that I have the authority and the autonomy
to do whatever I want.

813
01:04:11,581 --> 01:04:13,481
Don't I?

814
01:04:17,587 --> 01:04:20,249
- Don't I?
- <i>[Man] Absolutely, Mr. President. Absolutely. </i>

815
01:04:20,356 --> 01:04:23,223
- Don't I?
- <i>Ja. </i> Yes, sir.

816
01:04:23,326 --> 01:04:25,954
Don't I?

817
01:04:26,062 --> 01:04:28,223
Yes, you do.

818
01:04:31,300 --> 01:04:36,704
I will not be betrayed by a man as vulgar
and insidious as Cornelius Vanderbilt.

819
01:04:38,875 --> 01:04:41,002
I will, therefore,
revoke his permit.

820
01:04:42,111 --> 01:04:44,909
I will also commandeer his vessels.

821
01:04:45,014 --> 01:04:48,177
From this day on, they will be
the property of the Republic of Nicaragua.

822
01:04:48,284 --> 01:04:50,013
[Chuckles]
You cannot be serious.

823
01:04:50,119 --> 01:04:54,112
- Wanna bet?
- Surely, President Walker,
it might be more advantageous...

824
01:04:54,223 --> 01:04:56,123
<i>to be a little more diplomatic. </i>

825
01:04:56,225 --> 01:04:59,490
<i>Not to use force, but rather diplomacy. </i>

826
01:04:59,595 --> 01:05:01,927
For you, perhaps, but not for me.

827
01:05:02,031 --> 01:05:04,192
Excuse me, gentlemen.
I have work to do.

828
01:05:04,300 --> 01:05:07,861
Forgive me, sir, but I must contradict you.
Your work is here! Sir! Come back here!

829
01:05:07,970 --> 01:05:11,872
- <i>[Henningson Speaking Foreign Language]</i>
- I've had it with you, foreign weasel!

830
01:05:12,975 --> 01:05:16,672
<i>You have the nerve to come over here</i>
<i>barely speaking the language. </i>

831
01:05:16,779 --> 01:05:20,215
Taking our jobs!
Poleaxing our women! Take that!

832
01:05:20,316 --> 01:05:23,979
And that! And that!
You bastard!

833
01:05:24,086 --> 01:05:27,681
I cannot help noticing, sir,
during the time I've spent with you...

834
01:05:27,790 --> 01:05:32,193
that you've betrayed
every principle you've had...

835
01:05:32,295 --> 01:05:35,287
all the men who supported you.

836
01:05:35,398 --> 01:05:37,525
May I ask why?

837
01:05:37,633 --> 01:05:40,796
No, you may not.

838
01:05:40,903 --> 01:05:46,000
- [Muttering]
- <i>I'm still not clear on what exactly are your aims. </i>

839
01:05:47,176 --> 01:05:49,736
[Walker]
The ends justify the means.

840
01:05:49,845 --> 01:05:52,780
- What are the ends?
- [Walker] I can't remember.

841
01:05:54,583 --> 01:05:59,919
<i>[Vanderbilt] You two scumbags went</i>
<i>behind my back and cut into my action.! </i>

842
01:06:00,022 --> 01:06:04,118
Nobody does that!
Do you understand?

843
01:06:04,226 --> 01:06:07,787
Nobody fucks with Vanderbilt!

844
01:06:07,897 --> 01:06:11,856
<i>We are both sure, Commodore Vanderbilt, </i>
<i>that we can reach some sort of accommodation. </i>

845
01:06:11,968 --> 01:06:13,959
After all, we are all civilized men.

846
01:06:14,070 --> 01:06:16,595
Civilized men?

847
01:06:16,706 --> 01:06:20,767
From now on,
you're gonna be shoveling shit!

848
01:06:20,876 --> 01:06:25,210
And if your mouths are not too full of it,
you'll thank me for the privilege!

849
01:06:25,314 --> 01:06:30,081
- Thank you. Thank you, sir.
- That's how civilized I think you are!

850
01:06:30,186 --> 01:06:32,552
- Thank you, sir.
- [Shouts]

851
01:06:32,655 --> 01:06:35,351
- [Growls]
- <i>Thank you, Commodore. </i>

852
01:06:35,458 --> 01:06:37,824
You've not only betrayed
the commodore...

853
01:06:37,927 --> 01:06:43,388
you've betrayed yourselves by putting
faith in that lunatic extremist Walker.

854
01:06:43,499 --> 01:06:47,833
Now look.
You've upset the commodore.

855
01:06:47,937 --> 01:06:51,236
<i>What were you thinking of? </i>
<i>Did you seriously imagine... </i>

856
01:06:51,340 --> 01:06:54,036
this pathetic madman
was in charge down there?

857
01:06:54,143 --> 01:06:56,907
- No, of course not. We didn't...
- Get out of here!

858
01:06:57,013 --> 01:07:00,210
Both of you!
[Grunting]

859
01:07:00,316 --> 01:07:01,874
What should we do about Walker?

860
01:07:01,984 --> 01:07:04,714
- <i>[Train Passing]</i>
- <i>[Crossing Bell Ringing]</i>

861
01:07:06,822 --> 01:07:09,814
No one will remember Walker.

862
01:07:11,260 --> 01:07:16,197
No one will remember men who lose.

863
01:07:19,635 --> 01:07:22,365
<i>[Men Chattering]</i>

864
01:07:22,471 --> 01:07:24,598
[Woman Screaming]

865
01:07:24,707 --> 01:07:27,039
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Look at that fat cat Walker. </i>

866
01:07:27,143 --> 01:07:31,079
Struttin' about as if he was a king.

867
01:07:31,180 --> 01:07:34,672
One thing he didn't ken,
it's Vanderbilt that's runnin' the show.

868
01:07:35,785 --> 01:07:37,719
If he ever opposed the bloke...

869
01:07:37,820 --> 01:07:40,015
we'll be up to our necks in shit.

870
01:07:41,123 --> 01:07:43,114
What have I got, Doctor?

871
01:07:44,493 --> 01:07:46,393
It's cholera.

872
01:07:46,495 --> 01:07:49,396
[Laughing]

873
01:07:49,498 --> 01:07:52,023
[Sobbing]

874
01:07:52,134 --> 01:07:54,625
<i>[Woman Screaming]</i>

875
01:07:55,004 --> 01:07:58,030
- [Men] Hurrah!
- [Man] What means this shouting?

876
01:07:58,140 --> 01:08:01,371
I fear the people choose
Caesar as their king.

877
01:08:01,477 --> 01:08:03,809
- Hurrah!
- While men...

878
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:06,507
Ah! That's mine.

879
01:08:08,050 --> 01:08:10,211
Another general shout!

880
01:08:10,319 --> 01:08:12,480
[Screaming]

881
01:08:14,523 --> 01:08:19,119
<i>I do believe that these are for</i>
<i>some new honors heaped on Caesar. </i>

882
01:08:19,228 --> 01:08:23,494
<i>[Man #2] Why, man, he doth bestride</i>
<i>the narrow world like a colossus. </i>

883
01:08:23,599 --> 01:08:27,057
Hey, bring on the darky!

884
01:08:27,169 --> 01:08:29,069
- Hurrah!
- Hurrah!

885
01:08:29,171 --> 01:08:33,164
And we petty men
walk under his huge legs...

886
01:08:33,275 --> 01:08:35,402
<i>and peep about</i>
<i>to find ourselves... </i>

887
01:08:35,511 --> 01:08:37,445
[Officer] Where are you going?
[Groans]

888
01:08:37,546 --> 01:08:42,108
- [Man] You bastard!
- We are in crisis on all fronts.
We must have your attention.

889
01:08:42,218 --> 01:08:45,654
Is there no way you could not have
waited till at least intermission?

890
01:08:45,754 --> 01:08:48,655
- Shit!
- The men are going mad.

891
01:08:48,757 --> 01:08:52,193
They're defacing the cathedral,
pillaging the precious artifacts.

892
01:08:52,294 --> 01:08:54,956
<i>[Walker]</i>
<i>The priests must take their chances. This is war. </i>

893
01:08:55,064 --> 01:08:57,624
[Henningson] Mr. President,
the men are on the point of mutiny.

894
01:08:57,733 --> 01:09:01,499
- No, they are not.
- <i>[Henningson] Are you all right, sir? </i>

895
01:09:01,604 --> 01:09:06,132
- [Jones Muttering]
- Vanderbilt has diverted his steamships
to Panama, cut off our supplies!

896
01:09:06,242 --> 01:09:09,439
We have no new recruits, no money,
very little ammunition.

897
01:09:09,545 --> 01:09:11,445
<i>Very little ammunition.! </i>

898
01:09:11,547 --> 01:09:13,879
<i>[Cole]</i>
<i>We have lost control of León, Masaya... </i>

899
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:17,419
- Chinandega, Matagalpa...
- And every major Nicaraguan town.

900
01:09:17,520 --> 01:09:19,954
<i>[Bruno]</i>
<i>Rubbish. Defeatist nonsense.! </i>

901
01:09:20,055 --> 01:09:22,819
- Pure unadulterated horseshit!
- [German]

902
01:09:22,925 --> 01:09:25,120
- Food!
- Booze!

903
01:09:25,227 --> 01:09:27,127
- Money!
- Justice!

904
01:09:27,229 --> 01:09:30,630
[Together]
Food! Booze! Money! Justice!

905
01:09:30,733 --> 01:09:33,566
Food! Booze! Money! Justice!

906
01:09:33,669 --> 01:09:37,127
<i>Food.! Booze.! Money.! Justice.! </i>

907
01:09:37,239 --> 01:09:39,969
- You!
- What?

908
01:09:40,075 --> 01:09:43,044
- <i>Are a disgrace. </i>
- <i>I'm</i> a disgrace?

909
01:09:43,145 --> 01:09:47,548
<i>This whole operation is</i>
<i>a fucking disgrace, Your Worship.! </i>

910
01:09:47,650 --> 01:09:51,586
<i>You are stripped of your rank. You can either</i>
<i>stay here as a private or you can leave. </i>

911
01:09:51,687 --> 01:09:53,746
Hey, private this, Willie!

912
01:09:55,858 --> 01:09:57,758
Anderson.

913
01:09:57,860 --> 01:09:59,350
<i>[Crowd Gasping]</i>

914
01:09:59,461 --> 01:10:01,326
- Holy shit!
- Hey, hey, hey!

915
01:10:03,132 --> 01:10:05,191
- Ah, shit!
- Give me his medals!

916
01:10:05,301 --> 01:10:07,201
Give me his medals!
I want his medals!

917
01:10:07,303 --> 01:10:09,203
Mother never liked you anyway.

918
01:10:11,974 --> 01:10:14,534
Let me have men
about me that are fat.

919
01:10:14,643 --> 01:10:17,271
Yon Cassius has
a lean and hungry look.

920
01:10:17,379 --> 01:10:21,110
He thinks too much.
Such men are dangerous.

921
01:10:26,155 --> 01:10:28,453
Men...

922
01:10:28,557 --> 01:10:31,117
I have found a solution
to our problem.

923
01:10:33,229 --> 01:10:35,129
Slavery.

924
01:10:35,231 --> 01:10:37,631
[Excited Shouting]

925
01:10:40,536 --> 01:10:43,198
What do you mean?

926
01:10:44,306 --> 01:10:46,274
- We don't need no slaves!
- <i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

927
01:10:46,375 --> 01:10:48,639
- <i>We need money and weapons. </i>
- Fuck you, Walker.

928
01:10:48,744 --> 01:10:51,008
- And medicine.
- Silence!

929
01:10:52,615 --> 01:10:54,810
We will introduce
slavery into Nicaragua.

930
01:10:54,917 --> 01:10:57,852
<i>The South will have no choice</i>
<i>but to rally to our cause. </i>

931
01:10:57,953 --> 01:11:02,652
<i>[Crowd Shouting]</i>

932
01:11:02,758 --> 01:11:05,283
<i>[Cheering]</i>

933
01:11:08,731 --> 01:11:10,631
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

934
01:11:14,003 --> 01:11:15,971
[No Audible Dialogue]

935
01:11:48,937 --> 01:11:51,633
<i>[Thunder Rumbles]</i>

936
01:12:02,451 --> 01:12:05,352
<i>[Walker Narrating]</i>
<i>There were rumors that several neighboring</i>
<i>countries had invaded Nicaragua. </i>

937
01:12:05,454 --> 01:12:07,354
You can't do this to me.
I'm an American citizen!

938
01:12:07,456 --> 01:12:10,914
- <i>Walker sent out agents to see if this was true. </i>
- I have friends in high places!

939
01:12:11,026 --> 01:12:12,960
<i>None of the agents returned. </i>

940
01:12:13,062 --> 01:12:15,428
"The Indian of Nicaragua...

941
01:12:15,531 --> 01:12:19,023
"in his fidelity and docility
and in his capacity for labor...

942
01:12:19,134 --> 01:12:22,535
"approaches nearly the Negroes
of the United States.

943
01:12:22,638 --> 01:12:25,664
"In fact, the manners of the Indian
towards the ruling race...

944
01:12:25,774 --> 01:12:29,938
"are now more submissive than those
of the American Negro to his master.

945
01:12:34,717 --> 01:12:36,617
[Coughs]

946
01:12:40,422 --> 01:12:43,721
"The advantage of Negro
and Indian slavery in Nicaragua...

947
01:12:43,826 --> 01:12:46,090
"will therefore be twofold.

948
01:12:46,195 --> 01:12:49,858
"While it will furnish a certain labor
for the use of agriculture...

949
01:12:49,965 --> 01:12:51,933
"it will also tend
to separate the races...

950
01:12:52,034 --> 01:12:55,094
and destroy the half-castes
who cause the disorder."

951
01:13:03,445 --> 01:13:05,777
[Coughing]

952
01:13:09,385 --> 01:13:14,345
"The Battle of Rivas, June 29, 185 5.

953
01:13:16,658 --> 01:13:20,560
"Not more than a dozen went out
to drive away upward a hundred.

954
01:13:21,663 --> 01:13:24,689
"And their charge swept
the enemy completely away.

955
01:13:25,801 --> 01:13:27,928
"There was no thought of rank.

956
01:13:29,138 --> 01:13:32,073
"But each one went forth
with his revolver...

957
01:13:32,174 --> 01:13:35,769
"ready to do the part
of a true man in the fray.

958
01:13:38,680 --> 01:13:43,811
"Never have I seen a collection of such
brave men assembled under one banner.

959
01:13:45,821 --> 01:13:48,722
God bless them all."

960
01:13:48,824 --> 01:13:51,315
<i>[Gunshots In Distance]</i>

961
01:13:55,164 --> 01:13:58,930
- <i>[Gunshots Continue]</i>
- <i>[Henningson] I have studied with Josef Penn. </i>

962
01:13:59,034 --> 01:14:01,798
I have studied with Lubitsch
and von Koch!

963
01:14:01,904 --> 01:14:05,704
And you have the presumption
to talk to me of military tactics.

964
01:14:05,808 --> 01:14:08,709
- [Both Shouting]
- [Groans]

965
01:14:08,811 --> 01:14:11,837
[Shouts]

966
01:14:16,518 --> 01:14:20,318
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire In Distance]</i>
- Bruno... and the Germans...

967
01:14:20,422 --> 01:14:22,413
they have a vision.

968
01:14:24,927 --> 01:14:26,861
Always be a straight shooter, James.

969
01:14:26,962 --> 01:14:29,795
I like the sound of that.

970
01:14:29,898 --> 01:14:31,866
<i>[Floorboard Creaks]</i>

971
01:14:46,715 --> 01:14:49,013
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

972
01:14:55,824 --> 01:14:57,815
I must speak with you.

973
01:14:59,795 --> 01:15:01,956
- I don't understand.
- <i>There is no time. </i>

974
01:15:02,064 --> 01:15:03,964
You speak...

975
01:15:04,066 --> 01:15:08,469
I have spoken to you in many ways,
but you have not heard me.

976
01:15:10,038 --> 01:15:13,098
But now you must, Willians.

977
01:15:13,208 --> 01:15:15,233
Everything depends on it.

978
01:15:18,847 --> 01:15:20,974
Did you see this?

979
01:15:22,618 --> 01:15:24,518
<i>[Machine Gun Fire Continues]</i>

980
01:15:24,620 --> 01:15:28,112
I beg you. Please.

981
01:15:28,223 --> 01:15:32,091
If we have a lot of death,
we will have a revolution.

982
01:15:32,194 --> 01:15:35,357
We must not have that
if we are to survive.

983
01:15:35,464 --> 01:15:37,728
We are both aristocrats.

984
01:15:39,334 --> 01:15:41,359
I am not an aristocrat.

985
01:15:41,470 --> 01:15:44,405
I'm a social democrat.
What's the matter with you?

986
01:15:44,506 --> 01:15:46,940
[Spanish]

987
01:15:47,042 --> 01:15:50,443
I only want what is best for the
Nicaraguan people. I'm surprised at you.

988
01:15:52,281 --> 01:15:54,306
<i>Now leave me alone. </i>
<i>I have important work to do. </i>

989
01:15:54,416 --> 01:15:56,350
Are you quite sure of that?

990
01:15:56,451 --> 01:15:58,885
Absolutely! And shut the door
on your way out.

991
01:15:58,987 --> 01:16:00,887
Okay.

992
01:16:05,661 --> 01:16:08,425
<i>[Walker]</i>
<i>Bruno.! Bruno.! </i>

993
01:16:08,530 --> 01:16:10,293
<i>Mon général.! </i>

994
01:16:14,670 --> 01:16:17,730
Yrena, what are you doing? Bruno!

995
01:16:17,839 --> 01:16:19,807
<i>Général? </i>

996
01:16:23,412 --> 01:16:25,403
[Clicking]

997
01:16:29,051 --> 01:16:30,609
[Spanish]

998
01:16:30,719 --> 01:16:32,687
<i>[Footsteps Departing]</i>

999
01:16:36,224 --> 01:16:38,351
<i>[Footsteps Approaching]</i>

1000
01:16:39,561 --> 01:16:42,155
[Panting]

1001
01:16:43,966 --> 01:16:46,434
Instruct the men to burn the town.

1002
01:16:49,404 --> 01:16:51,372
- <i>Ja. </i>
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire Continues]</i>

1003
01:17:10,025 --> 01:17:11,993
[All Shouting]

1004
01:17:14,563 --> 01:17:16,758
[Shouting Orders, Indistinct]

1005
01:17:21,136 --> 01:17:23,104
What are you doing? Idiot!

1006
01:17:23,205 --> 01:17:26,606
- You are an idiot! Idiot! Idiot!
- <i>[Man Laughing]</i>

1007
01:17:26,708 --> 01:17:29,336
What is this?
[Shouting]

1008
01:17:33,115 --> 01:17:36,141
[Laughing]

1009
01:17:49,831 --> 01:17:51,799
[No Audible Gunshots]

1010
01:17:51,900 --> 01:17:54,368
[No Audible Dialogue]

1011
01:18:06,782 --> 01:18:08,875
<i>[Bomb Whistling]</i>

1012
01:18:09,985 --> 01:18:12,954
<i>[Woman Screaming]</i>

1013
01:18:15,557 --> 01:18:17,957
- <i>[Gunshot]</i>
- <i>[Explosion]</i>

1014
01:18:21,496 --> 01:18:23,157
[Laughs]

1015
01:18:27,836 --> 01:18:29,736
[Whinnies]

1016
01:18:34,676 --> 01:18:35,768
[Groans]

1017
01:18:47,756 --> 01:18:49,724
[Indistinct]

1018
01:19:00,902 --> 01:19:02,631
[Shouting, Indistinct]

1019
01:19:02,738 --> 01:19:04,706
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

1020
01:19:13,849 --> 01:19:17,717
<i>[Air Raid Siren Wailing]</i>

1021
01:19:30,432 --> 01:19:32,400
<i>[Siren Continues]</i>

1022
01:19:54,389 --> 01:19:57,381
<i>[Crowd Chanting]</i>
<i>Walker.! Walker.! Walker.! </i>

1023
01:19:57,492 --> 01:20:00,893
<i>Walker.! Walker.! Walker.! </i>

1024
01:20:00,996 --> 01:20:04,261
<i>[Chanting Continues]</i>

1025
01:20:08,970 --> 01:20:11,200
<i>[Chanting Stops]</i>

1026
01:20:47,309 --> 01:20:50,005
[No Audible Gunshots]

1027
01:21:05,527 --> 01:21:07,495
[No Audible Dialogue]

1028
01:21:08,597 --> 01:21:10,588
[Groans]

1029
01:21:16,071 --> 01:21:18,039
[No Audible Dialogue]

1030
01:21:26,648 --> 01:21:30,106
You men, get the colonel's
brother's body outta here.

1031
01:21:59,848 --> 01:22:03,511
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>
- <i>[Man Screams]</i>

1032
01:22:09,024 --> 01:22:11,549
<i>[Bomb Whistling]</i>

1033
01:22:11,660 --> 01:22:13,628
<i>[Woman Wailing]</i>

1034
01:22:15,430 --> 01:22:17,398
<i>**[Children Singing, Faint]</i>

1035
01:22:17,499 --> 01:22:19,967
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>
- <i>[Man Screams]</i>

1036
01:22:21,436 --> 01:22:23,233
Mr. President.

1037
01:22:23,338 --> 01:22:26,671
- It's been a long time, Doctor.
- It doesn't seem like it.

1038
01:22:26,775 --> 01:22:28,766
[Screaming]

1039
01:22:31,346 --> 01:22:33,610
- <i>[Henningson] Mr. President. </i>
- Yes.

1040
01:22:33,715 --> 01:22:36,741
Granada has been put to the torch.

1041
01:22:36,851 --> 01:22:40,685
- How many have we lost?
- <i>[Hornsby] Nearly all, sir. </i>

1042
01:22:40,789 --> 01:22:42,654
We must leave immediately.

1043
01:22:42,757 --> 01:22:45,851
- I will speak to my men one last time.
- Immediately!

1044
01:22:45,961 --> 01:22:49,488
- I insist, Major.
- Sir, I... [Groans] My arm!

1045
01:22:49,597 --> 01:22:51,565
<i>[Woman Screaming]</i>

1046
01:22:52,667 --> 01:22:55,192
Immortals, attention!

1047
01:23:04,713 --> 01:23:08,513
Unless a man believes that there is
something great for him to do...

1048
01:23:08,616 --> 01:23:11,551
he can do nothing great.

1049
01:23:11,653 --> 01:23:14,520
A great idea springs up
in a man's soul.

1050
01:23:14,622 --> 01:23:17,147
It agitates his entire being.

1051
01:23:17,258 --> 01:23:19,419
Transports him
from the ignorant present...

1052
01:23:19,527 --> 01:23:22,087
and makes him feel
the future in a moment.

1053
01:23:23,965 --> 01:23:28,095
Reduced to our present position
by the cowardice of some...

1054
01:23:28,203 --> 01:23:31,229
the incapacity of others
and the treachery of many...

1055
01:23:31,339 --> 01:23:33,330
we are yet writing
a page in history...

1056
01:23:33,441 --> 01:23:36,342
that it will be impossible
to forget or erase.

1057
01:23:40,415 --> 01:23:44,215
<i>You all might think</i>
<i>that there will be a day... </i>

1058
01:23:44,319 --> 01:23:48,255
<i>when America will leave</i>
<i>Nicaragua alone. </i>

1059
01:23:48,356 --> 01:23:52,019
<i>But I am here to tell you, flat out... </i>

1060
01:23:52,127 --> 01:23:54,254
<i>that that day will never happen... </i>

1061
01:23:54,362 --> 01:23:57,422
<i>because it is</i>
<i>our destiny to be here. </i>

1062
01:23:57,532 --> 01:24:00,228
<i>It is our destiny</i>
<i>to control you people. </i>

1063
01:24:01,336 --> 01:24:04,100
<i>So no matter how much you fight, </i>
<i>no matter what you think... </i>

1064
01:24:04,205 --> 01:24:06,173
<i>we'll be back... </i>

1065
01:24:08,143 --> 01:24:10,703
<i>time and time again. </i>

1066
01:24:12,113 --> 01:24:15,446
By the bones of our American dead
in Rivas and Granada...

1067
01:24:16,551 --> 01:24:20,078
I swear that we will never abandon
the cause of Nicaragua.

1068
01:24:22,991 --> 01:24:26,483
Let it occupy your every
waking and sleeping thought.

1069
01:24:29,597 --> 01:24:32,589
From the future,
if not the present...

1070
01:24:32,700 --> 01:24:35,134
we may expect a just judgment.

1071
01:24:35,236 --> 01:24:37,204
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

1072
01:24:37,305 --> 01:24:39,273
<i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>

1073
01:24:42,844 --> 01:24:47,213
- * Onward Christian soldiers *
- <i>[Bomb Whistling]</i>

1074
01:24:47,315 --> 01:24:51,809
* Marching as to war *

1075
01:24:51,920 --> 01:24:56,380
- * With the cross ofJesus *
- <i>[Bomb Whistling]</i>

1076
01:24:57,492 --> 01:25:00,359
- [Man] What about the prisoners?
- [Walker] Shoot them!

1077
01:25:00,462 --> 01:25:03,022
[Hornsby] You heard the colonel.
Shoot the prisoners!

1078
01:25:03,131 --> 01:25:06,794
- * Christ the royal master *
- <i>[Gunshots]</i>

1079
01:25:06,901 --> 01:25:12,032
- <i>[Man Screams]</i>
- * Leads against the foe *

1080
01:25:12,140 --> 01:25:16,668
* Forward into battle *

1081
01:25:16,778 --> 01:25:21,147
* See his banner go *

1082
01:25:21,249 --> 01:25:25,618
* Onward Christian soldiers *

1083
01:25:25,720 --> 01:25:30,282
* Marching as to war *

1084
01:25:30,391 --> 01:25:35,124
- * With the cross ofJesus *
- <i>[Helicopter Whirring]</i>

1085
01:25:35,230 --> 01:25:39,690
* Going on before **

1086
01:25:39,801 --> 01:25:41,769
<i>[Helicopter Whirring]</i>

1087
01:25:43,905 --> 01:25:45,964
<i>**[Continues, Indistinct]</i>

1088
01:26:11,432 --> 01:26:13,366
I have been instructed
by the State Department...

1089
01:26:13,468 --> 01:26:15,402
of the United States of America...

1090
01:26:15,503 --> 01:26:18,870
to return all American citizens
to their homeland.

1091
01:26:18,973 --> 01:26:21,441
[Excited Shouting]

1092
01:26:22,477 --> 01:26:25,037
Yes!
Sorry, only U.S. citizens.

1093
01:26:28,650 --> 01:26:30,914
<i>Only U.S. citizens. </i>

1094
01:26:31,019 --> 01:26:34,887
That's it.
U.S. citizens! U.S. citizens.

1095
01:26:34,989 --> 01:26:37,719
Get your hands off me!
Goddamn it, get 'em off!

1096
01:26:37,825 --> 01:26:39,952
<i>[Man Shouting In Spanish]</i>

1097
01:26:40,061 --> 01:26:42,359
Shoot him! Shoot him!

1098
01:26:42,463 --> 01:26:44,055
- <i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>
- [Screams]

1099
01:26:45,633 --> 01:26:47,601
<i>[Screams]</i>
<i>My arm.! </i>

1100
01:26:50,838 --> 01:26:52,772
Please, listen to me.

1101
01:26:52,874 --> 01:26:54,899
[Screaming]

1102
01:26:55,009 --> 01:26:57,944
What is your nationality, sir?

1103
01:26:58,046 --> 01:27:00,947
I'm William Walker, president
of the Republic of Nicaragua!

1104
01:27:01,049 --> 01:27:03,017
I'm sorry, sir.

1105
01:27:04,352 --> 01:27:06,752
Move it out!

1106
01:27:18,466 --> 01:27:20,696
Colonel!

1107
01:27:22,203 --> 01:27:24,194
<i>[Machine Gun Fire]</i>

1108
01:27:43,157 --> 01:27:47,184
<i>[Man Shouting Orders In Spanish]</i>

1109
01:27:50,098 --> 01:27:52,066
[Spanish]

1110
01:28:37,912 --> 01:28:41,211
Let me say to those who invoke
the memory of Vietnam...

1111
01:28:42,817 --> 01:28:45,217
there is no thought...

1112
01:28:45,320 --> 01:28:47,982
of sending American combat
troops to Central America.

1113
01:28:52,760 --> 01:28:55,388
[Man Announcing]
Maneuvers designated Operation Big Pine...

1114
01:28:55,496 --> 01:28:57,987
are being conducted less than 10 miles
from Honduras's border with Nicaragua.

1115
01:28:58,099 --> 01:29:02,297
Nicaraguans consider the exercise
a serious act of aggression.

1116
01:29:02,403 --> 01:29:05,736
The United States insists
the maneuvers are purely defensive.

1117
01:29:05,840 --> 01:29:09,139
This maneuver is designed to help
the Hondurans to defend their own country.

1118
01:29:10,411 --> 01:29:15,371
And it doesn't... it doesn't envision
any involvement of U.S. ground forces.

1119
01:29:17,185 --> 01:29:21,417
[Announcer] So far, 80,000 U.S. troops
have participated in the maneuvers.

1120
01:29:21,522 --> 01:29:23,581
Those leading the exercises
say it's all being done...

1121
01:29:23,691 --> 01:29:25,352
for the sake
of peace and self-defen...

